"title": "5370: kingship, human",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5370",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Human kings are to be respected. Israel demanded and received a king from God but the failure of kings after David led to the expectation of a coming great king in sucession to David.</p>\n<h2>Human kingship</h2>\n<h3>Human kingship is to be respected as ordained by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:1-Rom13:7\">ROM 13:1–13:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:1-1Tim2:2\">1TI 2:1–2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:13\">1PE 2:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:17\">1PE 2:17</a></p>\n<h3>Allegiance to God is greater than allegiance to human kings</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:47\">DAN 2:47</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:29\">ACT 5:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:23\">HEB 11:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:27\">HEB 11:27</a></p>\n<h2>Kingship in Israel</h2>\n<h3>Israel is ruled by God and his appointed leader</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:22-Judg8:23\">JDG 8:22–8:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:1\">JDG 19:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg21:25\">JDG 21:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:15-1Sam7:17\">1SA 7:15–7:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:12\">1SA 12:12</a></p>\n<h3>Israel demands and receives a king from God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:4-1Sam8:9\">1SA 8:4–8:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut17:14-Deut17:20\">DEU 17:14–17:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:19-1Sam8:22\">1SA 8:19–8:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:1\">1SA 10:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:17-1Sam10:19\">1SA 10:17–10:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:24\">1SA 10:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam11:14-1Sam11:15\">1SA 11:14–11:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:12-1Sam12:15\">1SA 12:12–12:15</a> <em>The demand for a king is seen as a rejection of God's rule but at the same time the king is seen as a gracious gift from God</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos13:10-Hos13:11\">HOS 13:10–13:11</a></p>\n<h3>David is Israel's greatest king</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:26-1Chr29:28\">1CH 29:26–29:28</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:10-1Kgs2:12\">1KI 2:10–2:12</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:70-Ps78:72\">PSA 78:70–78:72</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:13\">1SA 16:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:3-2Sam5:5\">2SA 5:3–5:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:3\">1CH 11:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:1-2Sam8:14\">2SA 8:1–8:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr18:1-1Chr18:13\">1CH 18:1–18:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:14\">1KI 3:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:6\">1KI 11:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:38\">1KI 11:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs14:3\">2KI 14:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:50\">PSA 18:50</a></p>\n<h3>God's covenant with David</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:8-2Sam7:16\">2SA 7:8–7:16</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:7-1Chr17:14\">1CH 17:7–17:14</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:4-1Kgs9:5\">1KI 9:4–9:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:17-2Chr7:18\">2CH 7:17–7:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:11-Ps132:12\">PSA 132:11–132:12</a></p>\n<h2>The failure of the kingship after David leads to the expectation of a future king like David</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:15\">JER 33:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:6-Isa9:7\">ISA 9:6–9:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:1-Isa11:5\">ISA 11:1–11:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa16:5\">ISA 16:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:5-Jer23:6\">JER 23:5–23:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer30:8-Jer30:9\">JER 30:8–30:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:23-Ezek34:24\">EZK 34:23–34:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:24-Ezek37:25\">EZK 37:24–37:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:11\">AMO 9:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic5:2-Mic5:5\">MIC 5:2–5:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:10\">MRK 11:10</a></p>\n<h2>Royal Psalms</h2>\n<p>These Psalms, although used for the king of the day, share the expectation of a greater future king. The NT regards them as fulfilled in Jesus Christ:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:6-Ps2:9\">PSA 2:6–2:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:1\">PSA 45:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps72:1\">PSA 72:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:1\">PSA 110:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:11\">PSA 132:11</a></p>",
